_source.aboutme_text:
A graduate of Istanbul Technical University and Bahcesehir University's MBA program, I'm a technology and entrepreneurship evangelist. In 2014, I received a masters degree at San Diego State University. I started a management trainee program at Abdi İbrahim Pharmaceuticals in Istanbul. In 2016, I joined Istanbul's Kolektif House, the city's premier co-working space, working initially with startups and eventually moving to oversee Isbank's Entrepreneurship Program. As the program coordinator for the entrepreneurship program, I worked with startups on business plans, scaling up, fundraising, and other challenges. In 2019, I joined 212, the first VC in Turkey. At 212, I generate the deal flow and support the portfolio. Apart from that, I am also leading the communications and marketing initiatives. 
In addition, I am also the coordinator of Fvckup Nights Istanbul, an event series where anyone can share stories of professional failure.
_source.focussingon_text: Currently, I am an Associate in 212, Istanbul-based VC fund. We invest in early & growth-stage tech companies typically in Seed & Series A rounds. Our strategy is to invest in B2B tech solutions that have demonstrated traction, a clear product-market fit, and readiness to scale globally.
_source.looking_for_text: Strategic partnerships for our portfolio companies, and startups to invest.
_source.networkreason_text: I would like to meet with APX portfolio that fits our investment criteria. I'm also looking for Growth partners for our portfolio to work with in Europe & USA.
Our company, Forloop, has recently joined the apx program :)

Ivan was previously an Investment Manager at Iconic Holding, where he was instrumental in setting up their crypto ETP practice and IC member and trader for their index funds, and the COO and Head of Research of Kintaro Capital, a crypto fund regulated by the MFSA, managing a team of five financial analysts researching and diligencing blockchain companies and cryptocurrencies. 

He holds a Master in Management with a specialization in Finance from ESMT Berlin.

_source.apxbio_text: Jakob is an Investment Manager at APX. He works closely with initial investments, from outreach to deal closure, to integrate them into APX’s portfolio. As a native Berliner, he shares insider tips for the local start-up scene. The unwavering commitment to changing the world is what drew Jakob to the start-up world. Before joining APX, Jakob worked at the international talent investor Entrepreneur First, the operational VC Project A, and various start-ups throughout northern Europe. He studied Corporate Management and Economics at Zeppelin University and holds an MBA from Copenhagen Business School. Away from his desk, Jakob likes to stay active. In addition to his love for skiing, he played field hockey for a long time, even coaching the next generation in the sport. Also enjoying working with his hands, Jakob crafts his own, albeit admittedly uncomfortable, furniture.

_source.aboutme_text:
James is an Investment Associate at APX. Working across all stages of the investment funnel, he tests start-up founders and analyses their business models and chosen markets. James is also responsible for supporting portfolio companies. He’s thrilled to be working at the forefront of innovation and engaging with ambitious founders.

Before joining APX, James was an analyst for Amplifier,  a supply chain-focused VC, and a business designer at Fjord, an international design studio. He also supported startups at the Founders Factory in London before moving to Berlin. During his bachelor’s at UCL, he built an e-commerce platform for emerging artists. Though born in the UK, James celebrates his Chinese heritage proudly; he is a co-founder of HOTPOT NETWORK, a community for overseas and European-born Chinese innovators.

Outside of work, James is an artist and stand-up comedian, sharing his talents across Berlin. Having always been passionate about entrepreneurship and creativity, he used to draw and print comic books at school and sell them to his classmates for 20 pence each. James is also a huge advocate for mental health.
_source.networkreason_text: Member of the APX team
